notes:
Final-gate additions for the sparse-intent contract:
- prove absent versus explicit-same-as-baseline remain distinct;
- prove a baseline change flows to inherited values but not pinned explicit values;
- prove reset removes intent rather than materializing baseline;
- prove invalid explicit input is surfaced rather than silently defaulted;
- prove default-document inference cannot grant completeness or editability;
- prove controls follow declared capability rather than kind/type labels.
Mars uses exact catalog parity and 16 recommendations; Zellij uses curated recommendations plus truthful native-file and opaque-state surfaces.

Additional final-gate contracts: prove an externally managed All-only field remains visible in Overview; prove reset shows the inherited value and origin before emitting unset; prove a localized invalid field and a wholly invalid document take distinct honest paths; and avoid wording that equates owner acceptance with operational correctness. Full provenance history remains out of scope.
